deck: Dennis Hopeless is the writer of Cable & X-Force and Avengers Arena.
description: Dennis Hopeless is more than a mild-mannered midwestern author. This is the man that transformed Arcade, Marvel's punchline villain, into an A-list threat. Thanks to Arcade's role as mastermind of the Avengers Arena series, fans voted him Marvel's 2nd-best villain of 2013.

deck: Colorist, letterer and self publisher. Works includes Marvel, DC, Random House and many Indie publishers. Now does work for Red Anvil comics and self publish comics under the banner Section 8 Comics. He also does web comics called @the8spot and The Hook Up. Also draws sketch cards.
description: Comic Book artist, Colorist, letterer and Self Publisher. Started working for Marvel comics as in intern in 1993 Worked for the conventions department. Designed poster, Post cards and other promo items for Marvel. By 1994, was hire full time to work the Art Returns Department. After 10 years working in the office, he left Marvel and went to become a full time freelance artist. He had done freelance for Marvel Comics, DC Comics, CMX Wildstorm, Dark Horse, Blue Water Comics, Committed Comics, Red Anvil Comics, RZG Comics, 11/88 Studios, Superverse Comics. He's also does Sketch cards for Topps, Upper Deck & Crypotozoic. He also self publish comics with Writer Eric Rivera for their comic company Section 8 Comics.
name: Wilson Ramos Jr.

deck: Writer and co-creator of Serpent Wars from AAM Markosia.  Our next book, The Chili will be with AAM Markosia as well, with an early 2011 release.  Chris is represented by Jeff Ross Management in California.
